title: tinycodet 0.4.5 (Under Development)
text: Slight speed improvement stri_locate_ith(). New Features: Added following functions “safer functionality” category: form(), aes_pro(), with_pro(), safer_partialmatch(). Naturally, added tests new functions.

title: tinycodet 0.4.1
text: CRAN release: 2024-02-17 Added explanation string overview help page, regarding usage vector recycling. Provided additional clarification help file %row% %col~% operators. Simplified internal code decimal ()equality testing operators. Added tests. Moved is_wholenumber() decimal truth testing section. Argument change: Added rt argument strfind()<-, moved rt arguments end functions. type argument strcut_brk() can now also directly accept list produced stringi::stri_opts_brkiter().

title: tinycodet 0.4.0
text: CRAN release: 2024-01-11 Clarified documentation %col~% %row~% strip attributes. Clarified usage merge = FALSE pattern charclass, documentation stri_locate_ith() function. Clarified documentation locked objects protected modification reference. Clarified documentation ‘stringi’ pattern searching infix operators p argument can also character vector length 1. Clarified stri_locate_ith() documentation one pass capture_groups argument; also clarified capture ith group using stri_locate_ith(). clarified stri_locate_ith() support long vectors. Normalized links “See Also” sections documentation. Renamed “str_truth” page “str_search”, makes little sense. Removed redundant stringi:: piece example code import_LL(). help file s_pattern functions now actually titled “s_pattern”. messages returned import_as() aliasing packages now slightly less verbose: removed line “Methods work like normally”, replaced line “Importing packages …” “Importing packages registering methods…”. strcut_brk() function now includes tolist argument return list. Moreover, n argument may now also specified (n = -1L default). safety checks: Improved safety malformed conditions transform_if() function. stri_locate_ith() now gives warning empty string pattern given. help.import() function now gives error neither topic/package /alias supplied, instead just silently nothing. %sget% %strim% operators now give explicit error message arguments proper lengths. Internal Re-write: stri_locate_ith() now partially re-written, now includes ‘C++’ code, making bit faster. Also cleaned internal code functions . Added dependency: ‘Rcpp’ now added dependency, due aforementioned partial re-write ‘C++’. New Features: Added %ss% collection string arithmetic operators, added strfind()<- method string search operators. One can now supply argument list right-hand side %s{}% operator. Supplying = "start" check pattern appears start string. Supplying = "end" check pattern appears end string. Optimization: Managed optimise stri_locate_ith() even . Optimised ‘subset_if’ operators bit . Also optimised %n&%, %sget%, %strim%, %=strtype% operators bit . Argument change: s_pattern functions now wrap additional arguments list user, case using vector arguments, preventing potential confusion. Argument change: type argument stri_locate_ith_boundaries() now mandatory argument; one can now also supply stri_opts_brikiter(), keep consistent rest ‘stringi’. Tests: Improved tests s_pattern operators. Added tests stri_locate_ith() using argument merge = FALSE. Added error check tests help.import(). Added tests unequal vector sizes logic operators. Added tests empty condition subsets transform_if(). Added tests new functionalities introduced version. Added tests malformed ‘stringi’ pattern searches relevant functions. Bug fix: small bug s_coll() worked properly assigned object (usual), called directly (like nested inside function). now fixed.

title: tinycodet 0.3.0
text: CRAN release: 2023-12-11 Expanded import system documentation. Also tweaked documentation import_as() make slightly clearer. Expanded documentation decimal_truth operators. import_as() now allow 10 packages loaded single alias, prevent abusive usage import_as(). import system now tiny safety checks, including checks widely known meta-packages (“fastverse”). pkg_get_deps() function now also shared_tidy argument ignore shared ‘tidyverse’ libraries (‘rlang’, ‘lifecycle’, ‘cli’, ‘glue’, ‘withr’). Also changed default values recom, rstudioapi arguments. Added pkg_get_deps_minimal() function. Also changed default arguments pkg_get_deps(). Changed error message wrong extension specifications: replaced “actual reverse-dependencies” “actual extensions”. Changed usage word “load” “import” import system documentation, avoid confusion concept loading package. Added pversion_ functions help checking package versions. Removed “versions” attribute alias objects, favour aforementioned pversion_ functions. Argument name change: import_as() function, changed argument name loadorder import_order, avoid confusion concept loading package. Tests: Added tests. Optimization: Minor optimizations import_* functions transform_if(). Bug fix: Fixed bug pkg_get_deps() didn’t properly ignore recommended R-packages recom = FALSE.
